description:
When it comes to taco lunching in SoMa, I'll rarely turn down a trip with office-mates to Uno Dos Tacos. 

// I despise Chipotle so if colleagues want to lose me they know exactly where to go.

// Garaje is basically the best thing ever but their cash only policy (despite having the technology to input orders on an iPad) makes it a thing I can only do if I prep my wallet in advance, which is pretty much never. 

// Uno Dos Tacos lands itself in between with tasty tacos, burritos, and salads that are affordable, quick, can be paid for by credit card and enjoyed on copious indoor/outdoor seating options. 

I love that their meals are filling (the burrito is the best bang for your buck) and that they have options for meat, fish, or veggie lovers doesn't hurt either. 

If there's a line it usually moves quickly and somehow the cashiers still manager to give each customer the attention they need, answer any questions, and make suggestions if you need 'em. 

Definitely take advantage of the sauces on the tables if you dine in. I squirt that biz on my jam like there's no tomorrow and it always tastes delicious despite the tendency of the veggie burrito to be kinda soupy sometimes (stupid healthy veggies).
